title: For Sale:  Vintage 1993  Sig Sauer p228, Mint Condition & all Original
postcontent: HIGHLY COLLECTIBLE VINTAGE SIG SAUER ! This one's a real gem:  a truly mint condition example, completely original finish, all original parts with matching serial numbers,  genuine 1993 West German manufactured  Sig Sauer P228 in 9mm. Impressed date stamp "KD" denotes a 1993 manufacture date, as does the corresponding serial number beginning with  "B 191."  It has the impressed Kiev Germany proofmarks along with the German Federal Eagle surmounted above the "N."  It comes with the original owners manual  and cardboard sales box which also contains the matching serial # for the gun.  I also have the two original Sig Sauer mags it came with, along with some of those 9mm "Black Talons"  that were controversial at that time in the early 90's, that also help unofficially date the gun.   But I am the original purchaser,  the only owner, and the only person who has ever even handled this firearm since its acquisition by me 23 years ago, so I know its provenance completely without any gaps or questions about its history whatsoever.  I purchased it in late 1993 in Orlando Florida. It was one of my very first semi-auto handguns, but at that time I was totally new to the gun world, and so I bought a lot of different guns at that time.  As I got more immersed into shooting sports and tried lots of different things,  I very quickly became a Glock admirer for personal carry (sorry, some  people just like that low bore axis), and this gun, after being shot no more than 3 or 4 times at the range in the first month or two I had it, quickly became an "inside-the- desk drawer- gun," and has remained that way for the last 20 plus years.  That's why it's so pristine:  It has no holster wear bc it was never holstered, the only barely visible wear it does have, are some very, very light and faint mini-scratches just from being picked up and put back in the drawer every now and then, and from being moved when I simply moved to different cities over my life .  But from the 3 or 4 times it may have been shot over twenty years ago, I doubt I put more than 200- 400 rounds in it total, so it has an extremely low round count.  It's still flawless, I just tested it recently with a new mag prior to placing this ad.  It is almost quite literally a gun that has been time capsuled for over 20 years.  I have more photos but apparently Armslist only lets you upload a single photo, so people who are serious potential purchasers may ask me to send extra pics directly to you
